    {
      "id": "ykqyhM6Q87zwJUZhpEoo4",
      "questionNumber": 6,
      "questionText": "The IUPAC name of the following compound is :<br>\n<picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/7km5fk0mrsc9d/76798cdb-9ace-477e-8e52-3d9da9f10120/bd37d810-d8b3-11e9-acf6-6d09a288f7f2/file-7km5fk0mrsc9e-320w.jpg\"><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/7km5fk0mrsc9d/76798cdb-9ace-477e-8e52-3d9da9f10120/bd37d810-d8b3-11e9-acf6-6d09a288f7f2/file-7km5fk0mrsc9e-500w.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 8th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 231 English\"></picture>",
      "options": [
        "3-Hydroxy-4-methylpentanoic acid",
        "4,4-Dimethyl-3-hydroxybutanoic acid",
        "2-Methyl-3-hydroxypentan-5-oic acid",
        "4-Methyl-3-hydroxypentanoic acid"
      ],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "iupac-nomenclature",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/7km5fk0ms0dx1/178e49d4-7639-40bb-b2d7-7757226dbc2e/9cf8ba50-d8b4-11e9-acf6-6d09a288f7f2/file-7km5fk0ms0dx2-320w.jpg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 500px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/7km5fk0ms0dx1/178e49d4-7639-40bb-b2d7-7757226dbc2e/9cf8ba50-d8b4-11e9-acf6-6d09a288f7f2/file-7km5fk0ms0dx2-500w.jpg\"><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/7km5fk0ms0dx1/178e49d4-7639-40bb-b2d7-7757226dbc2e/9cf8ba50-d8b4-11e9-acf6-6d09a288f7f2/file-7km5fk0ms0dx2-680w.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 8th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 231 English Explanation 1\"></picture>\n<br><b>Note :</b> \n<br><br>1. Here -OH and -COOH functional group present. And priority of -COOH group is higher so numbering start from -COOH group.\n<br><br>2. Here -COOH acts as main functional group and -OH acts as substitute. So we take prefix of -OH group (Hydroxy) and suffix of -COOH group (-oic acid).\n<br><br>3. Here two substitude -CH<sub>3</sub>(methyl) and -OH(Hydroxy) present. And 'H' of Hydroxy comes before 'm' of methyl in alphabetical order. So IUPAC name stars with Hydroxy substitude.\n\n<br><br><style type=\"text/css\">\n.tg  {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;}\n.tg td{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg th{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  font-weight:normal;overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg .tg-7btt{border-color:inherit;font-weight:bold;text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n.tg .tg-0pky{border-color:inherit;text-align:left;vertical-align:top}\n</style>\n<table class=\"tg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;\">\n<thead>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"tg-7btt\"></th>\n    <th class=\"tg-7btt\">Functional group (priority order)</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-7btt\">suffix(s)</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-7btt\">prefix</th>\n  </tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(1)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpnphcp/3a244065-8715-4bb9-8b04-0419903a872e/b56b0090-8f35-11ec-a918-532e52a0063e/file-1kzpnphcq.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpnphcp/3a244065-8715-4bb9-8b04-0419903a872e/b56b0090-8f35-11ec-a918-532e52a0063e/file-1kzpnphcq.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 8th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 231 English Explanation 2\"> </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"><b>Oic acid</b>(when carbon(C) of this functional group present in the main chain)<br>or<br><b>Carboxylic acid</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group is not present in the main chain) </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">Carboxy</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(2)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpnzht2/441ed497-3450-4ea2-9a04-0c56068636cd/cbdc6f70-8f36-11ec-a918-532e52a0063e/file-1kzpnzht3.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpnzht2/441ed497-3450-4ea2-9a04-0c56068636cd/cbdc6f70-8f36-11ec-a918-532e52a0063e/file-1kzpnzht3.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 8th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 231 English Explanation 3\"> </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">sulphonic acid</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">sulpho</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(3)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpo1x19/95ae67d6-ffec-4705-9a44-f999c83fb334/0f3de2d0-8f37-11ec-a918-532e52a0063e/file-1kzpo1x1a.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpo1x19/95ae67d6-ffec-4705-9a44-f999c83fb334/0f3de2d0-8f37-11ec-a918-532e52a0063e/file-1kzpo1x1a.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 8th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 231 English Explanation 4\"> </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"><b>Oic anhydrid</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group present in the main chain) <br>or<br><b>Carboxylic anhydride</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group is not present in the main chain) </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">$$ - $$</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(4)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpvjtwd/7f6f089d-c6fe-48b9-a1c4-595a3e306171/6149bcd0-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvjtwe.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpvjtwd/7f6f089d-c6fe-48b9-a1c4-595a3e306171/6149bcd0-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvjtwe.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 8th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 231 English Explanation 5\"></td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"><b>Oate</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group present in the main chain) <br>or<br><b>Carboxylate</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group is not present in the main chain) </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">$$ - $$</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(5)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpvhyj3/f2fd0132-de26-476f-a616-bb759c9e8742/2d3f49f0-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvhyj4.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpvhyj3/f2fd0132-de26-476f-a616-bb759c9e8742/2d3f49f0-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvhyj4.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 8th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 231 English Explanation 6\"> </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"><b>Oyl halide</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group present in the main chain) <br>or<br><b>Carboxyl halide</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group is not present in the main chain) </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">haloflormyl</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(6)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpvmmrd/c937a359-3ffe-4683-9bd3-3074eee29a56/af336a90-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvmmre.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpvmmrd/c937a359-3ffe-4683-9bd3-3074eee29a56/af336a90-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvmmre.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 8th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 231 English Explanation 7\"></td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"><b>amide</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group present in the main chain) <br>or<br><b>carbamide</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group is not present in the main chain) </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">carbamoyl</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(7)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">cynide ($$ - $$ C $$ \\equiv $$ N)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"><b>nitrile</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group present in the main chain) <br>or<br><b>carbonitrile</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group is not present in the main chain) </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">cyano</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(8)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpvotae/df9c34e4-532f-4453-a80e-a39f58a78c6f/ebdcbe60-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvotaf.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpvotae/df9c34e4-532f-4453-a80e-a39f58a78c6f/ebdcbe60-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvotaf.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 8th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 231 English Explanation 8\"></td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">Carbylamine</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">isocyano</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(9)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpvr75i/aa709c39-b3cb-474c-a088-787493f284bd/2e30b960-8f55-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvr75j.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpvr75i/aa709c39-b3cb-474c-a088-787493f284bd/2e30b960-8f55-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvr75j.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 8th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 231 English Explanation 9\"></td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"><b>al</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group present in the main chain) <br>or<br><b>Carbaldehyde</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group is not present in the main chain) </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">formyl (oxo)</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(10)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpvsokz/b5b4a5c1-59e5-4cd2-8160-01d5ef423466/5776ac30-8f55-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvsol0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpvsokz/b5b4a5c1-59e5-4cd2-8160-01d5ef423466/5776ac30-8f55-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvsol0.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 8th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 231 English Explanation 10\"></td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">one</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">oxo</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(11)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">$$ - $$ OH</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">ol</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">hydroxy</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(12)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">$$ - $$ SH</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">thiol</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">mercapto</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(13)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">$$ - $$ NH$$_2$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">amine</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">amino</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<br><p>From this table you can see -COOH has highest priority and -NH<sub>2</sub> has lowest priority among all functional groups.</p>",
